SIMPLE: resound
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Resound
<hw>Re*sound"</hw> <pr>(r?*zound")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Resounded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Resounding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>resounen</ets>, OF. <ets>resoner</ets>, F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧sonner</ets>, from L. <ets>resonare</ets>; pref.
<ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>sonare</ets> to sound, <ets>sonus</ets> sound.
See <er>Sound</er> to make a noise.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To sound
loudly; <as>as, his voice <ex>resounded</ex> far</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be filled with sound; to ring; <as>as, the woods
<ex>resound</ex> with song</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To be echoed; to be sent back, as sound.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Common fame . . . <xex>resounds</xex> back to them again.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To be mentioned much and loudly.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To echo or reverberate; to be resonant; <as>as, the
earth <ex>resounded</ex> with his praise</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resound</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Resound
<hw>Re*sound"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To throw back, or
return, the sound of; to echo; to reverberate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Albion's cliffs <qex>resound</qex> the rural lay.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To praise or celebrate with the voice, or the sound
of instruments; to extol with sounds; to spread the fame of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The man for wisdom's various arts renowned,⟦br⟧
Long exercised in woes, O muse, <qex>resound</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To echo; reecho; reverberate; sound.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resound</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Resound
<hw>Re*sound"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Return of sound; echo.</def>
<rj><au>Beaumont.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resource</ent>⟦br⟧
